<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1410,2014]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1734,1760]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hallowell" authorityYear="1844" box="[343,562,1735,1761]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Chamaeleo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[343,562,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Chamaeleo gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly found throughout most of sub-Saharan Africa, with the exception of the southernmost countries (
<bibRefCitation author="Tilbury, C." box="[514,671,1771,1797]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref40393" refString="Tilbury, C. (2018) Chameleons of Africa. An Atlas, Including the Chameleons of Europe, the Middle East and Asia. Second, thoroughly revised edition. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 643 pp." type="book" year="2018">Tilbury 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, it has two recognized subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="gracilis Hallowell, 1841" authorityName="Hallowell" authorityYear="1841" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Chamaeleo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="gracilis" subSpecies="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1217,1437,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. gracilis gracilis</emphasis>
Hallowell, 1841
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt, 1919" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1919" box="[392,786,1807,1833]" class="Reptilia" family="Chamaeleonidae" genus="Chamaeleo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="gracilis" subSpecies="etiennei">
<emphasis box="[392,609,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. gracilis etiennei</emphasis>
Schmidt, 1919
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[799,971,1807,1833]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904)</bibRefCitation>
noted 
<specimenCount box="[1051,1158,1807,1833]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="adult">two adult</specimenCount>
females of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chamaeleon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Chamaeleon gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from “Lembu, Serra de Selles” and “N’Dalla Tando” as well as 
<specimenCount box="[933,1047,1843,1869]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="adult">two adults</specimenCount>
of modest dimensions (unspecified sex) from “Rio Luinha” (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[429,586,1879,1906]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">Ferreira 1906</bibRefCitation>
). Among the extant specimens, MHNCUP/REP 294–296, REP 299 and REP 302 might correspond to the citations. Specimen MHNCUP/REP 293 was offered to Newton by Captain Trigo Teixeira, likely when the naturalist collected in 
<emphasis box="[691,778,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">fazenda</emphasis>
Hôcco. Recent phylogenetic studies by 
<bibRefCitation author="Main, D. C." box="[1234,1388,1951,1977]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref38340" refString="Main, D. C. (2019 a) A phylogeny of the genus Chamaeleo with investigation of cryptic speciation. Unpublished M. S. Thesis, University of Johannesburg, Johannesburg, vi + 86 pp." type="book" year="2019">Main (2019a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Main, D. C. &amp; Tilbury, C. &amp; van Vuuren, B. &amp; Tolley, K. A." box="[151,373,1987,2014]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="70" refId="ref38380" refString="Main, D. C., Tilbury, C., van Vuuren, B. &amp; Tolley, K. A. (2019 b) Phylogeny, species delimitation and ancestral biogeography in Chamaeleo. African Herp News, 72, 70." type="journal article" year="2019">
Main 
<emphasis box="[219,276,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
(2019b)
</bibRefCitation>
recovered three cryptic species within 
<taxonomicName box="[818,938,1987,2013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chamaeleon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[818,938,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Clade 1 from the southern regions of West Africa; Clade 2 from the borderlands between 
<collectingCountry box="[680,742,151,177]" name="Chad" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Chad</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry box="[797,1054,151,177]" name="Cameroon" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Republic of Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1436,151,177]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
and Clade 3 from the borderlands between 
<collectingCountry box="[639,712,187,213]" name="Kenya" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[767,871,187,213]" name="Tanzania" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. No material from 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1166,187,213]" name="Angola" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Angola</collectingCountry>
was accessed. 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[151,209,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
has previously treated the Angolan specimens as 
<taxonomicName box="[862,1079,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chamaeleon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="gracilis" subSpecies="etiennei">
<emphasis box="[862,1079,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C. gracilis etiennei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, following 
<bibRefCitation author="Tilbury, C." box="[1211,1381,223,249]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref40358" refString="Tilbury, C. (2010) Chameleons of Africa, an Atlas Including the Chameleons of Europe, the Middle East and Asia. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 831 pp." type="book" year="2010">Tilbury (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. The author had referred to it as a subspecies, although noting that varietal status might be more appropriate, pending further research. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Main, D. C." box="[375,528,295,321]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref38340" refString="Main, D. C. (2019 a) A phylogeny of the genus Chamaeleo with investigation of cryptic speciation. Unpublished M. S. Thesis, University of Johannesburg, Johannesburg, vi + 86 pp." type="book" year="2019">Main (2019a)</bibRefCitation>
did not analyze material from 
<collectingCountry box="[865,950,295,321]" name="Angola" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Angola</collectingCountry>
, the taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1437,295,321]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chamaeleon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="gracilis" subSpecies="etiennei">
<emphasis box="[1224,1437,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C. gracilis etiennei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unaddressed.
</paragraph>
